observations.reason:
For the unimplemented PPAs (e.g. Trainings) under the YRRP program of the Department of Agriculture RO8, similar trainings were already conducted by the different NGOs like CRS and ACTED in CY 2016 and 2017, from which the same target participants have benefited (Farmers), hence, budget for the said training, including the unutilized fund was already returned to the source agency;

Three facilities under the program facilities such as the Vermiculture, Wood Vinegar, Greenhouse remain idle after their initial operation and test run due to the lack of interest from the recipients; needs enhancement of facility (wood vinegar - condenser);

Machinery and Equipment under the Cassava and Corn Program is yet to operate as the procurement of electric power requirements and construction of additional facility are still on going.

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:
Revenue Collectors strictly comply with the daily remittance of collections in full amount to the Municipal Treasurer and likewise, the Municipal Treasurer to deposit all her collections intact daily, or not later than the next banking day;
Municipal Treasurer stop the issuance of accountable forms to accountable officers who have pending unremitted collections;
Revenue Collectors and the Municipal Treasurer properly record collections and remittances on the cashbooks in the manner they transpired; and consistently provide the actual dates of deposit of collections on the cashbook.

We recommended that the LCE direct the GAD Focal Person to:
ensure compliance with the 5% minimum budget allocation either as a separate GAD fund or by attributing the agencys PAPs to the GAD budget or a combination of both;
inform the concerned DILG Office in writing if there are changes in the DILG-endorsed GPB.

We recommended that the LCE direct:

the GSO together with the inventory committee to conduct the physical count of inventories accurately and completely in accordance with the above-mentioned provisions to fairly present the Inventory account in the financial statements; 

the GSO together with the Municipal Agriculturist immediately conducts physical count of the inventories and equipment in his custody; prepare and submit RIS and SSMI to the Municipal Accountant for proper recording;

the GSO to complete the distribution of the Agricultural and Marine Supplies and the Property and Equipment under the YRRP to the identified recipients per the approved Project Proposal (Annex A) of the MOA dated October 5, 2017, executed by the DA – RFO 8 and the MLGU – Quinapondan; and

the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to conduct a periodic reconciliation of the Inventory account to ensure that the balance of the said account on their separate records is reconciled at yearend.

